co), a group of more than thirty thousand small farmers and indigenous people from the northern Ecuadorian Amazon who continue to fight for reparations and remediation to this day.Eye-opening and galvanizing, Crude brings to light one of the least well-known but most important cases of environmental and racial injustice of our time.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Apr 2022) 0aIndians of South AmericazEcuadorzOrientexSocial conditionsvComic books, strips, etc. 0aLiability for oil pollution damageszEcuadorvComic books, strips, etc. 0aOil spillsxEnvironmental aspectszEcuadorzOrientevComic books, strips, etc. 0aPetroleum industry and tradexEnvironmental aspectszEcuadorzOrientevComic books, strips, etc. 0aPetroleum wastexEnvironmental aspectszEcuadorzOrientevComic books, strips, etc. 7aCOMICS & GRAPHIC NOVELS / Nonfiction / General.2bisacsh1 aChute, Hannah.1 aRoudeau, Damien.1 aTardy-Joubert, Sophie, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2021 Englishz978311075400108iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Political Science 2021 Englishz978311075417908iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Political Science 2021z9783110753943oZDB-23-PLW08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertPenn State University Press Complete eBook-Package 2021z978311074510840uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978163779012040uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781637790120423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781637790120/original  a978-3-11-074510-8  Penn State University Press Complete eBook-Package 2021b2021  a978-3-11-075400-1  EBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2021 Englishb2021  a978-3-11-075417-9  EBOOK PACKAGE Political Science 2021 Englishb2021  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_E